<p>I created loops to assign column values from a <code>data.frame</code> to a column of another <code>data.frame</code> based on some conditions: </p>  <pre><code>for ( lineTab1 in 1 : dim(tab1)[1] ) {   for ( lineTab2 in 1 : dim(tab2)[1] ) {     if ( tab1$id[lineTab1] == tab2$id[lineTab2]) &amp;       tab1$year[lineTab1] == tab2$year[lineTab2]) ) {   tab1$region[lineTab1] &lt;- tab2$region[lineTab2]) } } } </code></pre>  <p>My loops are too slow! The first <code>data.frame</code> (<code>tab1</code>) has 60,000,000 observations and the second <code>data.frame</code> (<code>tab2</code>) has 1000 observations. Is there a way to speed up these loops?</p>